<!-- 2020-12-21 -->
<!-- December 21, 2020 -->
	<tr>

<td>
<table width="100%" align="left" cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td>
<!--<img alt="" height="" src="/common/images/Amy-JEPS-2.jpg">-->
</td>
<td>

<blockquote class="pageMajorHeading">
<span class="copyrightText">December 21, 2020</span><br />
The Jepson eFlora Revision 8 was published in December 2020! One of the new species included is <a href="/eflora/eflora_display.php?tid=103540"><i>Ceanothus pendletonensis</i></a> (image courtesy of John Rebman). For the full details, please see the summary here:<a href="/eflora/supplement_summary.html#rev8"> https://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/eflora/supplement_summary.html</a>
	</blockquote>

</td>
	<td>
<a href="/eflora/eflora_display.php?tid=103540"><img alt="" height=150px src="/common/images/ceanothus.jpg"></a>
	</td>
</tr>
</table></td> </tr>


