<!-- start news item -->
<!-- 2020-11-02 -->
<!-- November 2, 2020 -->
<tr> <td>
<table width="100%" align="left" cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td>
<img alt="" height="" src="/common/images/activities/algae2020.jpg"></a>
</td>
<td>

<blockquote class="pageMajorHeading">
<span class="copyrightText">November 2, 2020</span><br />
Using seaweeds to read the history of the oceans! Kathy Ann Miller, Curator of Algae in the University Herbarium,
was featured in a colorful article in The Guardian speaking to the importance of collections for baseline understanding of
marine environments and how they are changing.  See news story <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/oct/27/what-victorian-era-seaweed-pressings-reveal-about-our-changing-seas">here</a>. Also, see our developing
California seaweed eFlora <a href="https://ucjeps.berkeley.edu/seaweedflora.html"> here</a>.</blockquote>
</td>

	<td>
<!--<a https://calphotos.berkeley.edu/cgi/img_query?enlarge=0000+0000+0315+2849"><img alt="" height="" src="/common/images/vaccinium.jpg"></a>-->
	</td>
</tr>
</table></td> </tr>
