<tr>
<td>
<!--<img alt="" height="" src="/common/images/Amy-JEPS-2.jpg">-->
</td>
<td>
<!-- 2018-08-15 -->
<!-- August 15, 2018 -->
<blockquote class="pageMajorHeading">
<span class="copyrightText">August 15, 2018</span><br />
The University and Jepson Herbaria recently completed a NPS funded project to database and image over 1000 specimens collected by John Muir and housed at the John Muir National Historic Site in Martinez, California. Specimens were collected in Canada and Indiana in 1864-1867 and on his world tour in 1903-1904. Many of the specimens were in poor condition and were carefully remounted by plant mounter extraordinaire, Ana Penny. The Muir specimens are accessible via our Specimen Portal: <a href="https://webapps.cspace.berkeley.edu/ucjeps/publicsearch/publicsearch/?collector=Muir&collector_qualifier=keyword&displayType=list&maxresults=100&start=1"> https://webapps.cspace.berkeley.edu/ucjeps/publicsearch/publicsearch/</a>
</blockquote></td>
	<td>
<img alt="" height="" src="/common/images/muir.jpg">
	</td>
</tr>
