		 <td height="40" valign="bottom"><span class="pageName"><strong>Featured Projects</strong></span></td>

		</tr>
		<tr>

		 <td valign="top">
		 <table width="100%" border="0">
 <tr>
 <td align="center" valign="top"><a href="/consortium/about.html"><img src="/common/images/ico_consortium.jpg" alt="Consortium of California Herbaria" width="55" height="55" border="0" /></a></td>
 <td valign="top" class="bodyText"><p>The <a href="/consortium/about.html"><strong>Consortium of California Herbaria</strong></a> serves as a gateway to information from California vascular plant specimens that are housed in herbaria throughout the state. The display now includes information from 1.8 million specimen records, all searchable through a single interface. <a href="/consortium/about.html"><strong>Read more...</strong></a> </p> </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
 <td align="center" valign="top"><a href="/Baldwin-Lab.html"><img src="/common/images/ico_tarweed.png" alt="Baldwin Lab" width="55" height="55" border="0" /></a></td>
 <td valign="top" class="bodyText"><p>Evolutionary and systematic studies of Californian vascular plants are a major research focus of the <a href="/Baldwin-Lab.html"><strong>Baldwin Lab</strong></a> in the Jepson Herbarium, where investigations of the highly diverse native tarweeds and their Hawaiian-silversword descendants continue apace. <a href="/Baldwin-Lab.html"><strong>Read more...</strong></a> </p> </td>
 </tr>
 </table>
